ued value. The same accrued balance remains claimable on repeated calls.","impact":"Any account with non-zero accrued rewards can repeatedly claim and drain LEND held by the router, including rewards attributable to other users.","paths":["User accrues positive `lendAccrued` once","User calls `claimLend` and receives full accrued amount","`lendAccrued[user]` is unchanged","User repeats claims until router LEND balance is exhausted"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-015","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Liquidity checks accept zero oracle prices, creating fail-open borrow authorization","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:431","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:445","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:460","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:152","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617"],"claim":"`getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` uses oracle prices without validating `price > 0`. If a market price returns `0`, borrow-side effects for that asset become `0`, and collateral checks can pass despite real economic risk.","impact":"During oracle outages/misconfiguration returning zero, users can borrow assets with effectively no borrow value added in checks, potentially extracting pool liquidity and creating bad debt.","paths":["Oracle returns 0 price for borrow market","User calls same-chain or cross-chain borrow","Borrow value contribution is computed as zero in liquidity check","Borrow proceeds while true collateralization is insufficient"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-016","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Borrow/redeem update accounting after external calls, leaving reentrancy window for callback-capable tokens","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:127","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:167","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:170","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:179"],"claim":"`redeem` and `borrow` perform external protocol/token calls before updating internal accounting (`totalInvestment`, `borrowBalance`), and no reentrancy guard exists. Callback-capable listed tokens can reenter while state is stale.","impact":"If a callback-capable market token is listed, an attacker contract may chain nested operations against stale balances to over-redeem/over-borrow relative to intended single-call limits.","paths":["Attacker triggers `borrow` or `redeem` via contract","External token/protocol call executes before accounting update","Callback reenters router and passes checks using stale state","Nested operations extract excess value"],"round":3,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-017","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain repay path incorrectly mutates same-chain borrow storage","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:472","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:475","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:492","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:497","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:425"],"claim":"Cross-chain repay flows call `CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal(..., _isSameChain=false)`, but the function always writes to same-chain `borrowBalance` (`removeBorrowBalance`/`updateBorrowBalance`) after repayment. This mixes cross-chain repayment results into same-chain debt storage.","impact":"Debt accounting becomes inconsistent: liabilities can be double-counted (same-chain + cross-chain) causing false shortfall/DoS/unfair liquidation, and full cross-chain repay can erase same-chain borrow records for the same market if present.","paths":["repayCrossChainBorrowInternal -> _handleRepayment -> CoreRouter.repayCrossChainLiquidation","CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal computes borrowedAmount from cross-chain path (`borrowWithInterest`)","function still updates/removes `borrowBalance[borrower][_lToken]` (same-chain slot)","Cross-chain state is also updated in `_updateRepaymentState`, creating divergent or duplicated debt state"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-018","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation uses seized-collateral quantity as debt repayment amount","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:276","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:355","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:464","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:467"],"claim":"`_executeLiquidationCore` encodes `payload.amount = seizeTokens` for `CrossChainLiquidationExecute`. The same `payload.amount` is forwarded in `LiquidationSuccess` and later used by `_handleLiquidationSuccess` as the repay amount (`repayCrossChainBorrowInternal(..., payload.amount, ...)`).","impact":"Debt repayment diverges from intended `repayAmount`: liquidators can seize collateral priced for one value while paying a different debt amount, leaving residual bad debt or extracting value depending on price/exchange-rate relationships.","paths":["Chain B: liquidateCrossChain(repayAmount)","_executeLiquidationCore computes `seizeTokens` and sends as payload.amount","Chain A seizes collateral and returns LiquidationSuccess with same payload.amount","Chain B `_handleLiquidationSuccess` treats payload.amount as debt repay amount"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-019","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Liquidation-failure refund attempts token payout without prior escrow","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:172","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:491","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:478","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:482"],"claim":"`liquidateCrossChain` does not escrow repay tokens up front, yet failure handling performs `safeTransfer(payload.amount)` to the liquidator in `_handleLiquidationFailure`. The refund amount originates from computed `seizeTokens`, not deposited funds.","impact":"If the token lookup resolves and router holds balance, attackers can trigger failing liquidations and drain router-held tokens without having prepaid; otherwise this contributes to stuck/failing failure-handling messages.","paths":["Attacker calls `liquidateCrossChain` (no token transfer from liquidator)","Cross-chain execution reaches failure branch and sends `LiquidationFailure`","Destination `_handleLiquidationFailure` transfers `payload.amount` to liquidator from router balance"],"round":4,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-020","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Borrowed-asset tracking can be cleared while debt still exists, hiding liabilities from liquidity checks","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:495","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:521","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:560","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:395","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:421"],"claim":"Repayment paths remove `userBorrowedAssets` membership for an lToken based on a single ledger becoming empty, without verifying all debt ledgers for that asset are zero. Since liquidity checks iterate only `userBorrowedAssets`, remaining same-chain or cross-chain debt can be omitted from borrow/withdraw risk checks.","impact":"A borrower can retain real debt that is no longer counted in `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`, enabling excess borrowing or redemption and creating bad debt/insolvency risk.","paths":["User has same-chain and cross-chain debt for lToken X -> fully repays same-chain debt -> `CoreRouter.repayBorrowInternal` removes borrowed-asset entry -> cross-chain debt for X is skipped in liquidity loop.","User has same-chain debt and one cross-chain record for lToken X -> full cross-chain repay path (`_updateRepaymentState` or `_handleDestRepayMessage`) removes borrowed-asset entry when that array length is 1 -> same-chain debt remains but is no longer included in liquidity accounting."],"round":5,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-021","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Redeem pays users using stale pre-accrual exchange rate, causing systematic underpayment","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:115","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:121","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:124"],"claim":"`redeem()` computes `expectedUnderlying` using `exchangeRateStored()` before calling `LErc20.redeem(_amount)`. `redeem` can accrue interest and realize a higher exchange rate, but the router transfers only the stale lower `expectedUnderlying` amount.","impact":"Redeemers can be consistently underpaid while surplus underlying remains trapped in router balances, creating direct user fund loss and accounting drift.","paths":["User calls `redeem(_amount, _lToken)` after accrual gap","Router snapshots stale exchange rate and computes `expectedUnderlying`","`LErc20.redeem` accrues and credits higher underlying to router","Router transfers only stale amount to user"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-022","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation credits seized collateral without registering liquidator supplied-asset membership","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:310","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:313","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:337","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:340"],"claim":"Same-chain and cross-chain liquidation paths increase liquidator `totalInvestment` for seized collateral but do not call `addUserSuppliedAsset(liquidator, lTokenCollateral)`. Liquidity logic iterates `userSuppliedAssets`, so these seized positions can be invisible to collateral accounting.","impact":"Liquidators may be unable to redeem seized collateral or may face distorted liquidity checks unless they had already registered that market, weakening liquidation usability and incentives.","paths":["Liquidation seizes collateral and only updates `totalInvestment` for liquidator","`userSuppliedAssets` is not updated for the seized market","Subsequent `redeem`/liquidity checks omit seized market collateral for that liquidator"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-023","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain liquidation can send unexecutable seize amount and revert on collateral-chain execution","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:268","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:274","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:333"],"claim":"`_executeLiquidationCore` forwards computed `seizeTokens` without bounding against borrower collateral on source chain. `_handleLiquidationExecute` then subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower `totalInvestment`; if `seizeTokens` exceeds balance, subtraction underflows and reverts.","impact":"Cross-chain liquidation messages can become revert-only, blocking liquidation completion and creating retry/stuck-message DoS behavior for unhealthy positions.","paths":["Liquidator initiates cross-chain liquidation with repay that maps to large `seizeTokens`","Router sends `CrossChainLiquidationExecute` with `payload.amount = seizeTokens`","Collateral-chain handler subtracts `payload.amount` from borrower collateral and reverts on underflow"],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-024","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Unbounded per-user asset-set iteration can gas-DoS risk checks and liquidation paths","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:170","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:180","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:394","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:421"],"claim":"`userSuppliedAssets` and `userBorrowedAssets` have no enforced upper bound, while `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral` iterates both sets with multiple external calls per item. Large user asset sets can push borrow/redeem/liquidation checks beyond practical gas limits.","impact":"Highly fragmented positions can become difficult or impossible to process, potentially preventing timely liquidation and increasing bad-debt risk for affected accounts.","paths":["User accumulates many supplied/borrowed markets","Any operation requiring liquidity checks calls `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`","Looped per-asset pricing/exchange-rate work exceeds gas budget and reverts"],"round":6,"source_agents":["opencode_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-025","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Cross-chain debt accrual uses local-chain borrow index instead of debt-chain index","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:491","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:499","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:722"],"claim":"Cross-chain borrow records persist `borrowIndex` captured from the remote debt market, but `borrowWithInterest` accrues those records with `LTokenInterface(_lToken).borrowIndex()` from the local-chain lToken passed by local accounting loops. For cross-chain borrows this can be a different market/index domain.","impact":"When the two chains’ borrow indices diverge, cross-chain liabilities are mispriced in risk checks. Under-accrual can allow excess borrowing/redeeming and create bad debt; over-accrual can cause unfair liquidations/DoS.","paths":["Source-chain `ValidBorrowRequest` stores `payload.borrowIndex` from destination debt market in `crossChainBorrows`.","Later, source-chain liquidity checks call `borrowWithInterest(account, localLToken)` via `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`.","`borrowWithInterest` multiplies by local `borrowIndex()` instead of the debt-chain market index basis of the stored record.","Computed debt deviates from true remote debt, breaking collateralization decisions."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-026","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Liquidation close-factor cap uses stale principal instead of accrued debt","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:341","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:353","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:354"],"claim":"In `liquidateBorrowAllowedInternal`, the maximum repay (`maxClose`) is computed from `borrowBalance.amount` (stored principal snapshot) rather than the borrower’s current accrued debt amount used for solvency evaluation.","impact":"After interest accrual, liquidation can be artificially capped below intended close-factor of actual debt, slowing deleveraging and increasing residual bad-debt risk for unhealthy accounts.","paths":["Borrow accrues interest so real debt grows above stored principal.","Liquidator calls same-chain liquidation.","Function computes `maxClose = closeFactor * borrowBalance.amount` (stale principal), not closeFactor times current debt.","Allowed repay can be materially too low, requiring extra transactions and delaying risk reduction."],"round":7,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-027","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Cross-chain borrow compares collateral and debt under different chain-local oracle domains","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:138","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:147","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:617","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:622","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:407","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:431"],"claim":"`borrowCrossChain` snapshots `payload.collateral` on source chain using source `priceOracle`, while destination validation computes `totalBorrowed` with destination `priceOracle`. The protocol does not normalize or attest valuation equivalence across chains before enforcing `payload.collateral >= totalBorrowed`.","impact":"If oracle configurations or freshness diverge between chains, borrowers can pass destination checks while being economically undercollateralized, creating cross-chain bad debt risk.","paths":["Source chain computes collateral value with source oracle and sends `payload.collateral`.","Destination computes borrow-side risk with its own oracle regime in `getHypotheticalAccountLiquidityCollateral`.","Mismatch in price domain allows `payload.collateral >= totalBorrowed` to pass under inconsistent valuations.","Borrow executes with weaker-than-intended collateralization."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-028","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"Shared router borrower account can hit Comptroller market-membership cap via permissionless borrow market selection","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:164","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:431","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:133","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:678"],"claim":"Borrow paths call `enterMarkets` for the router contract account (shared borrower in underlying markets), not per end-user. Since market membership has a finite cap, permissionless users can force the shared router into many markets and exhaust available membership slots.","impact":"After cap exhaustion, borrows that require adding a new market membership can fail for everyone, creating protocol-level availability degradation for additional markets.","paths":["Attacker performs dust borrows/cross-chain borrow flows across many listed markets.","Routers repeatedly call `enterMarkets` as the same router address.","Shared router membership set reaches Comptroller cap.","Subsequent borrow flows needing new market entry fail globally for that router."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-029","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Fixed LayerZero receive gas can make valid cross-chain messages unexecutable for large user state","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:405","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:544","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:581","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:818"],"claim":"`_send` hardcodes `addExecutorLzReceiveOption(1_000_000, 0)` for all message types, while receive handlers include variable-cost loops over per-user arrays (e.g., `_getBorrowDetails`, `_handleBorrowCrossChainRequest`, and repayment handlers). No per-message gas adaptation exists.","impact":"As user cross-chain position arrays grow, otherwise valid messages can repeatedly run out of gas on destination execution, causing stuck/retry-only operations and cross-chain flow DoS.","paths":["User/account accumulates many cross-chain borrow/collateral records.","Protocol sends message with fixed 1,000,000 gas option.","Destination handler loop cost exceeds budget and reverts.","Operational borrow/repay/liquidation flow remains failed until state/gas assumptions change."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-030","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Inbound cross-chain handlers hard-revert on state drift, enabling retry-stuck message DoS","locations":["LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:457","LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol:549"],"claim":"Receive-path handlers `_handleLiquidationSuccess` and `_handleDestRepayMessage` use strict `require(found, ...)` on mutable cross-chain position lookups. If the referenced position is already changed/removed before message delivery, the packet reverts instead of being idempotently ignored.","impact":"Stale or reordered packets can become persistently unexecutable, causing repeated retries and operational denial of service for affected cross-chain repay/liquidation finalization flows.","paths":["Operation A sends a cross-chain packet referencing a specific borrow/collateral record.","Before packet arrival, operation B repays/removes/reshuffles that record.","Receiver lookup returns `found == false`.","`require(found)` reverts, leaving the packet in failed/retry state."],"round":9,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-031","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Same-chain liquidation leaves zero-balance collateral markets in borrower supplied-asset set","locations":["LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:307","LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol:310"],"claim":"`liquidateSeizeUpdate` reduces borrower `totalInvestment` but does not remove the collateral market from `userSuppliedAssets` when the position is fully seized.","impact":"Zombie supplied-asset entries accumulate and permanently bloat collateral-iteration cost in liquidity checks, increasing practical gas-DoS risk for heavily liquidated users.","paths":["Borrower collateral in market M is fully seized via same-chain liquidation.","`totalInvestment(borrower, M)` becomes 0.","No `removeUserSuppliedAsset(borrower, M)` is executed in same-chain liquidation flow.","Future liquidity checks still iterate over zero-balance market entries."],"round":9,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]},{"id":"F-033","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Withdrawability helper can revert on zero denominator","locations":["LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:618","LayerZero/LendStorage.sol:621"],"claim":"`getMaxWithdrawable` computes `tokensToDenom = collateralFactor * exchangeRate * oraclePrice / 1e36` and divides by it without guarding for zero.","impact":"For markets with zero collateral factor and/or zero oracle price, this helper reverts and can break integrator flows relying on max-withdraw queries.","paths":["`collateralFactor == 0` or `oraclePrice == 0` for queried market.","`tokensToDenom` becomes zero.","`redeemableLTokens = (maxRedeemInUSD * 1e18) / tokensToDenom` divides by zero and reverts."],"round":9,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_layer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Cross-chain borrow does not re-validate collateral at execution on destination chain","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate of existing F-002 (stale collateral snapshot / TOCTOU)."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation validates health AFTER message sent, causing stale execution","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not a distinct new root cause; stale/liquidation-data issues are already captured (F-013/F-018), and the write-up misstates current execution checks."},{"title":"Same-chain borrow calculation rounds to zero enabling collateral bypass","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Insufficient code support for the claimed rounding-to-zero path; major borrow bypass already captured by F-001."},{"title":"Full repayment clears borrow records before verifying repay success","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Factually incorrect ordering: external repay is required first (`repayBorrow` at line 490), then storage removal occurs."},{"title":"Supply uses stale exchange rate for lToken calculation allowing underminting","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Duplicate root cause of existing F-008 (stale pre-mint exchange rate accounting mismatch)."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation doesn't verify collateral chain liquidity before sending","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Claim unsupported: seize path updates internal accounting, not collateral-chain token cash transfers requiring liquidity precheck."},{"title":"borrowForCrossChain missing zero address validation for borrower","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Low-value/unreachable in normal trusted-message flow; borrower is sourced from initiating user address, not arbitrary zero address."},{"title":"repayBorrow accepts any lToken without underlying existence validation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Unsupported-loss claim: invalid token address paths revert during SafeERC20 call execution rather than silently losing funds."},{"title":"LiquidateSeizeUpdate doesn't return actual seized amount to liquidator","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Not a security vulnerability; observability/API ergonomics only."},{"title":"Constructors accept any storage/oracle without contract validation","source_agents":["opencode_1"],"reason":"Deployment-time trust/admin configuration concern, not a protocol runtime exploit under normal governance assumptions."},{"title":"Cross-chain liquidation message can be built with zero destination lToken and guaranteed fail on receiver","source_agents":["codex_1"],"reason":"Primarily owner/mapping misconfiguration hardening issue; lacks a strong permissionless exploit path beyond self-failing operations."}]}
